{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_322","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented prompt 45 end to end and checkpointed the code at `dd7228ce348d7d414728d242336ada4fc52f3f8b` with `feat(prompt-45): pitch refinement via chat`.\n\nThe change adds a first-class `refine_pitch` action through the backend intent/action pipeline, a durable `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/pitches/refine` flow, pitch lineage/rationale persistence in hydrated session snapshots, and frontend wiring for both direct pitch refinement in the pitch stage and confirm-first chat actions in the chat lane. Earlier pitch batches are preserved instead of overwritten, and selected/refined pitch events now echo back into chat.\n\nVerification completed:\n- `cd backend && pytest` -> `140 passed, 5 skipped`\n- `cd backend && python -m ruff check app tests` -> passed\n- `cd frontend && npm run test` -> `14 passed`, `65 passed`\n- `cd frontend && npm run lint` -> passed\n- `cd frontend && npm run build` -> passed\n- Browser QA via Puppeteer in the live browser container passed, including screenshots for before refine, after refine, and persisted reload state:\n  - `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt45-ui-refinement-before.png`\n  - `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt45-ui-refinement-after.png`\n  - `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt45-ui-refinement-persisted.png`\n\nOne repo-level limitation remains: `make check` still stops at backend format-check because of unrelated pre-existing Ruff formatting drift outside this prompt’s scope. I documented that explicitly.\n\nThe required reviewer summary was written as the final step to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/45_pitch_selection_and_refinement_via_chat/summary.md)."}}
